description:
https://twitch.tv/TheLiveCoders

14 speakers over 14 hours, split into two streams.

Jones S Cropper - Developing tools for developers
Mary Jo Staebler - Using a boilerplate to create a WordPress Plugin
Trezy - Ally from the ground up
Nick Larsen - Reproducing AlphaZero
Andy Morrell - Finding your niche to stay relevant, in your career
Nina Zakharenko - Debugging Python: Goodbye Print, Hello Debugger
Jochen Lillich - How to build up resilience and keep burnout at bay
Carey Payette - Using Azure IoT Central to form a basis for your IoT Solution
Timmy Kokke - How to build a WebXR Game in 13KB
Ted Young - That's Not OOP: Getters and Setters are Still Evil
Michael Crump - Azure for Developers: In Plain English
Mahmood Hikmet - The Trolley Problem Problem: Talking about the Ethics of Self Driving Cars
Liz Phillip - Getting your Second Coding Job
Suz Hinton - Techniques for Interacting with Microcontrollers in the Browser
title: (Affiliated) The Live Coders Conference
